This paper deals with indexing and processing highly dynamic data in a streaming setting, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of multicore processors to accelerate stream processing is a topic of interest in parallel computing (cs.DC) and performance evaluation (cs.PF). Finally, the design of a concurrency control mechanism is relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
